{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778980656430,"sessionID":"ses_1cc8c890cffeH7ZgkwLy9vUwvP","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_tdHtXdDTuP04UUnZz8e1stqm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Obsoleted `GO:0010381` in favor of `GO:7770065` and committed the ontology changes locally.\n+\n+I also removed the old `never_in_taxon` constraints attached to `GO:0010381`, since leaving those on an obsolete term causes validation failures.\n+\n+Direct annotation impact checked before obsoletion:\n+- 1 direct annotation found in AmiGO: `TAIR:AT2G26350` / `PEX10`, evidence `IMP`, reference `PMID:17215364`\n+\n+Per the discussion on this ticket, that annotation should now be moved to `GO:7770065` once available in downstream annotation systems.\n+\n+Please keep the issue open until the annotation move is complete.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Obsoleted `GO:0010381` (`peroxisome-chloroplast membrane tethering`) and set a direct replacement to `GO:7770065` (`peroxisome-chloroplast membrane tether activity`).\n+\n+Summary of changes:\n+- Updated `GO:0010381` to `name: obsolete peroxisome-chloroplast membrane tethering`\n+- Preserved the historical definition with the required `OBSOLETE.` prefix\n+- Added an obsoletion comment explaining that the old term represented a molecular function\n+- Added `replaced_by: GO:7770065`\n+- Added the issue tracker link to `https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31877`\n+- Removed the obsolete term's synonym and asserted parent, following GO obsoletion practice\n+- Removed four `never_in_taxon` rows for `GO:0010381` from `src/taxon_constraints/never_in_taxon.tsv`\n+- Regenerated the derived taxon-constraint artifacts so the obsolete term no longer carries inherited taxon-constraint superclass axioms\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- The issue and follow-up comments make clear that 